post_text:
North Dakota Reading Corps is seeking tutors to help Ellendale Elementary School Kindergarten through Third Grade students succeed in school by giving them the extra support they need in learning how to read for the 2020-21 school year. Reading Corps tutors work one on one with a caseload of students for 20 minutes sessions each, on a set daily schedule. This part-time AmeriCorps position requires a commitment for the entire school year, 5 days a week. Tutors working during the school day while school is in sessions. Ellendale School is looking for one tutor to serve 20 hours per week. As an AmeriCorps tutor, you will receive a monthly living allowance of $820 and an education award of $2,360 to be used for college tuition and current student loans. Tutors who are 55 or older may choose to transfer their education award to a child, grandchild, or foster child.

Interested candidates must apply at www.ndreadingcorps.org. If you have questions about this position you may contact Mr. Michael Kaiser at michael.kaiser@ellendale.k12.nd.us or phone at (701) 349-3232.

post_text:
Sports Physical Info for 20-21:
Pre-participation Physical Examinations completed for the 2019-20 school year will be accepted during the 2020-21 school year upon submission of a parent and athlete signed waiver (previously known as Form B). These forms can be found by clicking on the Forms button at the bottom of the EPS School Athletics webpage: www.ellendale.k12.nd.us/athletics/.

If students did not get a physical last year, they will need to have one this year before they are allowed to practice or play in any sport. Phone numbers for the local clinics are: Avera - 349-3666 and Sanford - 349-3331.

All schools’ (Ellendale, Edgeley, Kulm) athletic facilities will remain closed for the month of June. This includes gyms, weight rooms, and practice fields.

Administrators will re-evaluate at the end of June to determine athletic facility use for the month of July.

There is a virtual Summer Athletic Program offered for the month of June. Please contact Allison Radermacher at aradermacher@ellendale.k12.nd.us to sign up.

**This is based on CDC guidelines, recommendations, and the ND Smart Restart plan.

shared_text:
Prince of Peace Care Center
May 4 at 8:31 PM ·

Our residents have enjoyed #gramsforgrands so much they have decided to return the favor! 💕The 3rd grade class from EHS has blessed the EP residents all year. Prior to #COVID19, they visited monthly to read 📚 books, bake cookies 🍪, and play BINGO together! Now they will be getting some mail back 💌! Hopefully this is the beginning of a long pen pal relationship! #bridgingthegenerationalgap ￼

Dickey County Leader, Ellendale ND
March 26 at 5:13 PM ·

Despite the closure, Sara Kuntz, Peggy Brandenburger, Lorraine Betting, and Norma Trautmann stay busy from 8:00 to 1:00 school days preparing and handing out meals for Ellendale Public School students and for anyone up to age 18, regardless of enrollment status. Lunch AND breakfasts are included in the daily distribution (lunch for today and breakfast for the next day).

Thanks for all the hard work. Also thanks to our bus drivers, who are delivering meals to rural pick-up points.

To be included in the program, go online here and fill out this simple form. https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe5WjOgePeB-58C95cvdbaiGReP_Rt3EKRini_50Aw-3hvXXA/viewform

post_text:
March 15, 2020 - 9:00 PM

Ellendale Public School will be closed Monday, March 16th - Friday, March 20th. The closure was ordered by North Dakota Governor Doug Burgum in response to the Coronavirus pandemic.

Gov. Doug Burgum announced the closures in a press conference earlier tonight. See the full press conference here (https://www.facebook.com/ndhealth/videos/562636674345087/)

Burgum said, "The strategy around the school closing is to reduce the rate of infection to allow us to have a week to plan, not just for how we deliver school services, but for us to plan to make sure that our health care system can take care of those that are most vulnerable."

More information will be released as it becomes available.

Sincerely,

Michael Kaiser, Superintendent
Ellendale Public School

shared_text:
ND Department of Public Instruction
February 5 at 5:04 PM ·

State Superintendent Kirsten Baesler congratulated 65 North Dakota high school seniors who have been nominated for United States Presidential Scholar honors.

The scholars were chosen from 20 public and four nonpublic high schools. Bismarck Century has the most nominees, with 13, while Grand Forks Central has 10. Fargo’s Davies and North high schools have six nominees each.

The U.S. Department of Education’s announcement of the 65 nominees is the beginning of the process of selecting one young man and one young woman as North Dakota’s two Presidential Scholars. Those choices will be announced in early May.

Full listing of nominees: https://www.nd.gov/dpi/news/nd-presidential-scholar-nominees-announced

November 26, 2019 at 2:20 PM ·

Please join us in congratulating Abigail Peterson and Isabella Ferderer, recipients of the SRCTC November Award of Excellence!! Abigail is a junior at Ellendale High School and is enrolled in Culinary Arts and Agriculture Education at SRCTC with Mrs. Kemmer and Mr. Spellerberg. She is the daughter of Steven and Christine Peterson of Fullerton. Isabella is a freshman at North Sargent High School in Gwinner and is enrolled in Agriculture Education with Mr. Zetocha. She is the daughter of Chris and Christina Ferderer of Gwinner. Congratulations to Abigail and Isabella on a job well done!
